		content: 'Title: Making AI work for you: How Onepoint does it\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Summary:\n' +
		  'AI is transforming the way enterprises operate. But are you harnessing its full potential? In this session, Shashin Shah and Chris Wray give a glimpse into how Onepoint applies AI for business use cases to create value for our clients and ourselves.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  "What you'll learn\n" +
		  '\n' +
		  "- Making AI work: While most AI conversations dwell on possibilities, this session dives into practical outcomes. Learn how AI can streamline operations, reducing costs and enhancing efficiency. We unpack Onepoint's proven approach to applying AI with a sharp focus on business value, not just the tech.\n" +
		  '\n' +
		  '- AI offerings to turn ideas into reality: Discover how Onepoint’s AI Expert services and AI Co-Lab turn ideas into scalable solutions. Witness how our pre-built series of AI Apps and the engine that underpins them help clients to adopt AI faster without starting from scratch.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  '- Real-world applications: Explore how AI can be applied to diverse domains through practical use cases. Get an inside look at how our Data Wellness tool (Onepoint D-Well™) uses AI to assess and improve enterprise data management and the Responsible AI tool (Onepoint Res-AI™), curated with expert knowledge.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  '- Future implications: Learn how to move confidently from legacy ways of working to AI-ready frameworks. Walk away with practical insights on implementing AI responsibly and how to prepare your organisation for the next wave of AI innovation.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Featured speakers\n' +
		  '- Shashin Shah\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  '- Chris Wray\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Who is this for\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'This session is ideal for business leaders, non-technical staff, AI and data specialists, and technology leaders looking to maximise the potential of AI and unlock real value. Business leaders and decision-makers will also benefit from the discussion on driving innovation with AI.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Session transcript:\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Si Sultan\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  "We've got a little bit of a new platform to contend with; hopefully, fingers crossed. The technology will be with us today and working with us. If not, then please indulge us. Give us some leeway on that. If everybody can mute what they’re saying while Shashin and Chris are talking this morning, we’ll have it. We’ll have time for a Q&A session at the end. And I would ask, please, that you hold your questions, because there’s a lot of material to cover, and I don’t want to steal their thunder. So I will hand over to Shashin now and put myself on mute. Shashin.\n" +
		  '\n' +
		  'Shashin Shah\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Thank you, Si. Good morning, everybody, and thank you for giving us this opportunity to share some of our learnings and experiences in applying AI, both internally within the organisation and also for some of our clients. So this morning, basically, it’s Chris Wray who will actually be doing a joint presentation with me. So what is it that we want to cover? At a very high level, I’ll explain in detail exactly what we’re covering today. We’ll introduce brief information on the company. We’ll then talk a little bit about AI in terms of what we’ve been doing and also sort of present our strategy and explanation of some of our services. But the majority of the time, frankly, is going to be spent on trying to show demos, which brings out the learnings from AI and artificial intelligence to some real-life problems. So we’ll spend the bulk of the time on that. We’ll then talk a little bit about some of our offerings and how we’re taking those to the market for some of our clients, and then, of course, a question and answer session towards the end. So in terms of what we are covering today, really, Chris and I will give you an overview of how we are applying AI for business use cases to create real value for our clients and ourselves. We’ll walk through and demo a series of examples. We want to avoid death by PowerPoint. So we’ll jump into some live demos. And I hope the demos will cooperate. They always have a tendency to do their own thing during live demos. And these are some of the things we actually want to try and present. In a sense, it’s based on some real-world tools, architectures, and frameworks we’re using. We’re actually looking at how to apply AI to solve legacy issues and, of course, have architectures that can deliver\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Cannot convert  \n' +
		  'The image quality is insufficient for accurate text extraction.Here’s the extracted text in markdown format:\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  '\n' +
