		  '\n' +
		  'Onepoint launches a comprehensive AI Ecosystem for the Boomi platform to accelerate enterprise automation and value creation with AI\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'London, United Kingdom - 13 May 2025 - Onepoint, an award winning technology consultancy specialising in enterprise-grade solutions, today announced the launch of Onepoint AI Ecosystem for Boomi, its Artificial Intelligence (AI) Ecosystem built on the Boomi platform. This collection of components, comprising Onepoint AI Connectors, Onepoint AI Workflows, and Onepoint AI Agents, is designed to help businesses build and run AI-driven automation and agent workflows faster and with reduced technical debt.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  '“The rise of agentic AI presents significant opportunities for automation and efficiency. The components of the Onepoint AI Ecosystem for Boomi are designed to automate complex tasks, simplify interactions with enterprise systems, provide valuable insights, and ultimately save time and reduce manual effort and errors across different business functions”, said Miguel Vale, Principal Solution Architect & AI Ecosystem Futurist at Onepoint. “As of today, Onepoint has developed circa 40 AI agents and other components for the Boomi platform, making Onepoint a leading partner of Boomi AI implementations.”\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'The Onepoint AI Ecosystem for Boomi provides a layered approach to incorporating agentic AI into enterprise workflows. At the foundational level are the Onepoint AI Connectors, described as the "nuts and bolts". These are Boomi-friendly integrations that enable secure communication between AI agents and databases, systems, or tools. Key connectors built by Onepoint include the OP Intelligence Connector, which allows switching between Large Language Models (LLMs), and supports external tools and actions such as updating CRMs or triggering workflows and creating embeddings. The OP Database Connector facilitates the building of RAG-based (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) systems, adding support to vector stores and similarity searches, direct connections to structured data, supporting relational databases, and enabling agents to read schemas, generate rules, and execute SQL in real-time.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Built on these connectors are the Onepoint AI Workflows. These are reusable "smart blocks" designed to make decisions and perform tasks typically requiring human effort, such as interpreting data, detecting Personally Identifiable Information (PII), and generating SQL.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'The top layer consists of Onepoint AI Agents. These production-ready solutions are usually created by combining Onepoint AI Workflows into functional, extensible flows.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Examples of the growing list of AI agents demonstrate their usefulness for diverse business use cases:\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  '- The AWS Resource Spinner agent automates the design and deployment of scalable Amazon Web Services infrastructure, spinning up resources like EC2, RDS, S3, Load Balancers, and even Boomi atoms. It enables instant provisioning based on user specifications through conversational interaction.\n' +
		  '- The ServiceNow Incident Management agent streamlines incident handling through natural language allowing users to create, update, list, and summarize incidents easily. It supports filtering, adding comments, and retrieving details—enabling faster, more intuitive support and enhancing the customer experience.\n' +
		  '- The Hotel Matcher agent uses OP Intelligence and OP Database connectors to enable dynamic RAG-based hotel matching through AI and vector similarity search. It identifies hotel names from text, handles misspellings and finds the best matching vector embeddings and cosine similarity. The final decision comes from the LLM—without relying on SQL or fuzzy logic.\n' +
		  '- The SAP Low Stock Purchase Recommendation agent intelligently detects low stock and suggests purchase orders based on sales trends, vendor lead times, and safety stock levels. It retrieves key details like material and vendor IDs by name, recalculates reorder timing, and helps procurement managers automate and optimise replenishment decisions using real-time insights.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  'Evaluation Warning: The document was created with Spire.Doc for Python.\n' +
		  '\n' +
		  "Onepoint's experts will demonstrate the Onepoint AI Ecosystem for Boomi at Boomi World 2025, the premier conference for Boomi’s customers and partners, in Dallas, Texas, from 12-15 May 2025.\n" +
