ssed. The technology will be with us today and working with us. If not, then please indulge us. Give us some leeway on that. If everybody can mute what they’re saying while Shashin and Chris are talking this morning, we’ll have it. We’ll have time for a Q&A session at the end. And I would ask, please, that you hold your questions, because there’s a lot of material to cover, and I don’t want to steal their thunder. So I will hand over to Shashin now and put myself on mute. Shashin.\\n\\nShashin Shah\\n\\nThank you, Si. Good morning, everybody, and thank you for giving us this opportunity to share some of our learnings and experiences in applying AI, both internally within the organisation and also for some of our clients. So this morning, basically, it’s Chris Wray who will actually be doing a joint presentation with me. So what is it that we want to cover? At a very high level, I’ll explain in detail exactly what we’re covering today. We’ll introduce brief information on the company. We’ll then talk a little bit about AI in terms of what we’ve been doing and also sort of present our strategy and explanation of some of our services. But the majority of the time, frankly, is going to be spent on trying to show demos, which brings out the learnings from AI and artificial intelligence to some real-life problems. So we’ll spend the bulk of the time on that. We’ll then talk a little bit about some of our offerings and how we’re taking those to the market for some of our clients, and then, of course, a question and answer session towards the end. So in terms of what we are covering today, really, Chris and I will give you an overview of how we are applying AI for business use cases to create real value for our clients and ourselves. We’ll walk through and demo a series of examples. We want to avoid death by PowerPoint. So we’ll jump into some live demos. And I hope the demos will cooperate. They always have a tendency to do their own thing during live demos. And these are 